1
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:05,480
How to Get a Free Meal.

2
00:00:05,480 --> 00:00:09,059
Even if your options are limited and your
pockets are turned inside out, you can still

3
00:00:09,059 --> 00:00:10,460
rustle up some grub.

4
00:00:10,460 --> 00:00:14,419
Consider several ways to feed yourself without
begging or stealing.

5
00:00:14,419 --> 00:00:20,990
You will need Fast food shops Grocery store
coupons Local bars with happy hours Nature

6
00:00:20,990 --> 00:00:28,150
preserves Public functions Restaurants Charitable
organizations and blood drives.

7
00:00:28,150 --> 00:00:29,300
Step 1.

8
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:34,460
Find or ask for free meal coupons from Mcdonald's,
the Cracker Barrel, and other restaurants.

9
00:00:34,460 --> 00:00:38,820
Look for scratch-off cards and contests to
win free food.

10
00:00:38,820 --> 00:00:39,820
Step 2.

11
00:00:39,820 --> 00:00:43,980
Search for local restaurants that offer free
birthday meals -- usually supplied only if

12
00:00:43,980 --> 00:00:46,760
you are accompanied by a friend who buys their
own.

13
00:00:46,760 --> 00:00:51,100
Some honor veterans, women, and seniors on
certain days of the year.

14
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:52,100
Step 3.

15
00:00:52,100 --> 00:00:53,640
Hang out at bars during happy hour.

16
00:00:53,640 --> 00:00:57,260
Buy a cheap drink for the opportunity to feast
for a couple hours.

17
00:00:57,260 --> 00:00:58,470
Step 4.

18
00:00:58,470 --> 00:01:03,960
Crash wedding receptions, wakes, church functions,
company picnics, and public promotional giveaways.

19
00:01:03,960 --> 00:01:08,170
Tour major food stores on weekends for promotional
sample displays that might comprise a full

20
00:01:08,170 --> 00:01:09,170
meal when you're done.

21
00:01:09,170 --> 00:01:14,110
Stick around a friend's home until you overstay
your welcome or clean out their pantry.

22
00:01:14,110 --> 00:01:15,280
Step 5.

23
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:19,440
Volunteer to help a charitable organization
and you can usually get fed, because there

24
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:20,990
is no other pay.

25
00:01:20,990 --> 00:01:24,640
Donate blood, as well, for which you will
be given sustenance afterward, and still feel

26
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:27,170
good about what you've done to help others.

27
00:01:27,170 --> 00:01:28,250
Step 6.

28
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:32,260
Scavenge in the woods for wild edibles that
you can take home, and cook.

29
00:01:32,260 --> 00:01:36,360
Hunt for game if you don't mind cleaning and
cooking it.

30
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:37,600
Step 7.

31
00:01:37,600 --> 00:01:41,830
Grow your own garden to get quality, fresh,
and safe food at little cost.

